\f1\fs48 \cf2 Installation: Famous 5-minute install\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420
\ls1\ilvl0
\f0\fs28 \cf3 {\listtext	1.	}Unzip the package in an empty directory and upload everything.\
{\listtext	2.	}Open {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "file:///Applications/MAMP/htdocs/amalaraqs.com/cms/wp-admin/install.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 wp-admin/install.php}} in your browser. It will take you through the process to set up a 
\f2 wp-config.php
\f0  file with your database connection details.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\sl420
\ls1\ilvl1\cf3 {\listtext	1.	}If for some reason this doesn't work, don't worry. It doesn't work on all web hosts. Open up 
\f2 wp-config-sample.php
\f0  with a text editor like WordPad or similar and fill in your database connection details.\
{\listtext	2.	}Save the file as 
\f2 wp-config.php
\f0  and upload it.\
{\listtext	3.	}Open {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "file:///Applications/MAMP/htdocs/amalaraqs.com/cms/wp-admin/install.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 wp-admin/install.php}} in your browser.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	3.	}Once the configuration file is set up, the installer will set up the tables needed for your blog. If there is an error, double check your 
\f2 wp-config.php
\f0  file, and try again. If it fails again, please go to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wordpress.org/support/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 support forums}} with as much data as you can gather.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf3 {\listtext	4.	}If you did not enter a password, note the password given to you.
\b0  If you did not provide a username, it will be 
\f2 admin
\f0 .\
{\listtext	5.	}The installer should then send you to the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "file:///Applications/MAMP/htdocs/amalaraqs.com/cms/wp-login.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 login page}}. Sign in with the username and password you chose during the installation. If a password was generated for you, you can then click on 'Profile' to change the password.\
\pard\pardeftab720

\f1\fs48 \cf2 Updating\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa260

\f0\b\fs32 \cf3 Using the Automatic Updater\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa280

\b0\fs28 \cf3 If you are updating from version 2.7 or higher, you can use the automatic updater:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420
\ls2\ilvl0\cf3 {\listtext	1.	}Open the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "file:///Applications/MAMP/htdocs/amalaraqs.com/cms/wp-admin/update-core.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 wp-admin/update-core.php}} in your browser and follow the instructions.\
{\listtext	2.	}You wanted more, perhaps? That's it!\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa260

\b\fs32 \cf3 Updating Manually\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl420
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0\fs28 \cf3 {\listtext	1.	}Before you update anything, make sure you have backup copies of any files you may have modified such as 
\f2 index.php
\f0 .\
{\listtext	2.	}Delete your old WordPress files, saving ones you've modified.\
{\listtext	3.	}Upload the new files.\
{\listtext	4.	}Point your browser to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "file:///Applications/MAMP/htdocs/amalaraqs.com/cms/wp-admin/upgrade.php"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 /wp-admin/upgrade.php}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa260

