\f1\fs48 \cf2 Online Resources\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa280

\f0\fs28 \cf3 If you have any questions that aren't addressed in this document, please take advantage of WordPress' numerous online resources:\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://codex.wordpress.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 The WordPress Codex}}\
The Codex is the encyclopedia of all things WordPress. It is the most comprehensive source of information for WordPress available.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wordpress.org/news/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 The WordPress Blog}}\
This is where you'll find the latest updates and news related to WordPress. Recent WordPress news appears in your administrative dashboard by default.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://planet.wordpress.org/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 WordPress Planet}}\
The WordPress Planet is a news aggregator that brings together posts from WordPress blogs around the web.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://wordpress.org/support/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 WordPress Support Forums}}\
If you've looked everywhere and still can't find an answer, the support forums are very active and have a large community ready to help. To help them help you be sure to use a descriptive thread title and describe your question in as much detail as possible.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://codex.wordpress.org/IRC"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 WordPress IRC Channel}}\
There is an online chat channel that is used for discussion among people who use WordPress and occasionally support topics. The above wiki page should point you in the right direction. ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "irc://irc.freenode.net/wordpress"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 irc.freenode.net #wordpress}})\
\pard\pardeftab720

\f1\fs48 \cf2 XML-RPC and Atom Interface\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa280

\f0\fs28 \cf3 You can post to your WordPress blog with tools like {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://download.live.com/writer"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Windows Live Writer}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://illuminex.com/ecto/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Ecto}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://bloggar.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 w.bloggar}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://radio.userland.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Radio Userland}} (which means you can use Radio's email-to-blog feature), {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.newzcrawler.com/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 NewzCrawler}}, and other tools that support the blogging APIs! :) You can read more about {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://codex.wordpress.org/XML-RPC_Support"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 XML-RPC support on the Codex}}.\
\pard\pardeftab720

\f1\fs48 \cf2 Post via Email\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa280

\f0\fs28 \cf3 You can post from an email client! To set this up go to your "Writing" options screen and fill in the connection details for your secret POP3 account. Then you need to set up 
\f2 wp-mail.php
\f0  to execute periodically to check the mailbox for new posts. You can do it with {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cron"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 cron}}-jobs, or if your host doesn't support it you can look into the various website-monitoring services, and make them check your 
\f2 wp-mail.php
\f0  URL.\
Posting is easy: Any email sent to the address you specify will be posted, with the subject as the title. It is best to keep the address discrete. The script will 
\i delete
\i0  emails that are successfully posted.\
\pard\pardeftab720

